Note: Parser Tests
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies parser builds AST for "CC = gcc".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse, assert ast_root non-null via assert_not_null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "CC = gcc" -> non-null AST, passed
- Parser returns null -> failure
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_simple_variable" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test parser generation of AST for simple variable assignment.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "CC = gcc"

    Let lexer_ptr be proc create_lexer from MakefileLexer
    Let tokens be proc scan from MakefileLexer with lexer_ptr, source

    Let parser_ptr be proc create_parser from MakefileParser with tokens
    Let ast_root be proc parse from MakefileParser with parser_ptr

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Parser creates AST for simple variable", ast_root

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies parser builds AST for target rule with multiple deps and
TAB-prefixed recipe.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse "app: main.o utils.o\n\tgcc -o ...", assert AST non-null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Target rule with 2 deps and 1 recipe -> AST non-null, passed
- Parser drops dep -> may still have non-null AST but shape wrong
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_target_rule" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test parser generation of AST for target rule with dependencies and recipes.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "app: main.o utils.o\n\tgcc -o app main.o utils.o"

    Let lexer_ptr be proc create_lexer from MakefileLexer
    Let tokens be proc scan from MakefileLexer with lexer_ptr, source

    Let parser_ptr be proc create_parser from MakefileParser with tokens
    Let ast_root be proc parse from MakefileParser with parser_ptr

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Parser creates AST for target rule", ast_root

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies parser builds AST for pattern rule with % and automatic
variables.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse "%.o: %.c\n\tgcc -c $< -o $@", assert AST non-null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Pattern rule -> AST non-null, passed
- Parser fails on % -> AST null
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_pattern_rule" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test parser generation of AST for pattern rule.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "%.o: %.c\n\tgcc -c $< -o $@"

    Let lexer_ptr be proc create_lexer from MakefileLexer
    Let tokens be proc scan from MakefileLexer with lexer_ptr, source

    Let parser_ptr be proc create_parser from MakefileParser with tokens
    Let ast_root be proc parse from MakefileParser with parser_ptr

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Parser creates AST for pattern rule", ast_root

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies parser handles conditional block with else branch.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse ifeq/else/endif source, assert AST non-null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Conditional with else -> AST non-null, passed
- Parser fails on "else" -> AST null
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_conditional" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test parser generation of AST for conditional block.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "ifeq ($(DEBUG),1)\nCFLAGS += -g\nelse\nCFLAGS += -O2\nendif"

    Let lexer_ptr be proc create_lexer from MakefileLexer
    Let tokens be proc scan from MakefileLexer with lexer_ptr, source

    Let parser_ptr be proc create_parser from MakefileParser with tokens
    Let ast_root be proc parse from MakefileParser with parser_ptr

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Parser creates AST for conditional", ast_root

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies parser handles .PHONY and similar special targets.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse ".PHONY: clean all\nclean:\n\trm -f *.o", assert AST non-null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- .PHONY target -> AST non-null, passed
- Parser fails on "." prefix -> AST null
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_special_target" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test parser generation of AST for special targets like .PHONY.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be ".PHONY: clean all\nclean:\n\trm -f *.o"

    Let lexer_ptr be proc create_lexer from MakefileLexer
    Let tokens be proc scan from MakefileLexer with lexer_ptr, source

    Let parser_ptr be proc create_parser from MakefileParser with tokens
    Let ast_root be proc parse from MakefileParser with parser_ptr

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Parser creates AST for special target", ast_root

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Translator Tests
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies AST -> HIR translation for ":=" variable assignment.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Lex+parse+translate "CC := gcc"; assert HIR non-null and no errors.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- ":=" assignment -> HIR non-null with no errors, passed
- Translator returns null or sets errors -> failure
@End TestCases

Process called "test_translator_variable_to_hir" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test AST→HIR translation for variable assignments.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "CC := gcc"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let hir_root be proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Translator creates HIR for variable", hir_root

    Let has_errors be proc has_errors from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr
    Let _no_err be has_errors is equal to 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Translation has no errors", _no_err, "No errors"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies AST -> HIR translation for target rule with recipe.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Translate "app: main.c\n\tgcc -o app main.c"; assert HIR non-null
and no errors.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Target rule -> HIR non-null, no errors, passed
- Translator drops recipe -> may still succeed
@End TestCases

Process called "test_translator_target_to_hir" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test AST→HIR translation for target rules.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "app: main.c\n\tgcc -o app main.c"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let hir_root be proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Translator creates HIR for target", hir_root

    Let has_errors be proc has_errors from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr
    Let _no_err be has_errors is equal to 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Translation has no errors", _no_err, "No errors"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies AST -> HIR translation for ifdef conditional block.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Translate "ifdef DEBUG\nCFLAGS = -g\nendif"; assert HIR non-null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- ifdef block -> HIR non-null, no errors, passed
- Translator drops the inner assignment -> HIR shape wrong
@End TestCases

Process called "test_translator_conditional_to_hir" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test AST→HIR translation for conditionals.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "ifdef DEBUG\nCFLAGS = -g\nendif"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let hir_root be proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    proc assert_not_null with suite_ptr, "Translator creates HIR for conditional", hir_root

    Let has_errors be proc has_errors from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr
    Let _no_err be has_errors is equal to 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Translation has no errors", _no_err, "No errors"

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Backend Tests
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Verifies the HIR -> Makefile backend produces non-empty output for
a variable assignment.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Translate "CC = gcc" to HIR, regenerate, assert output length > 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Variable HIR -> non-empty regenerated output, passed
- Backend produces empty string -> "Output not empty" assertion fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_backend_variable_generation" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test HIR→Makefile generation for variables.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "CC = gcc"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let hir_root be proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Let regenerated be proc hir_to_makefile_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, hir_root

    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Backend generates non-empty output for variable", is_valid, "Output not empty"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies the backend produces output containing a TAB character for
the recipe line, which is semantically required by Make.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Translate target rule to HIR, regenerate; assert output non-empty
AND contains tab character.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Target rule HIR -> regenerated has TAB, passed
- Backend uses spaces instead of TAB -> "Contains tab character" fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_backend_target_generation" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test HIR→Makefile generation for targets.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "app: main.o\n\tgcc -o app main.o"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let hir_root be proc makefile_to_hir_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Let regenerated be proc hir_to_makefile_with_emitter from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, hir_root

    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Backend generates non-empty output for target", is_valid, "Output not empty"

    Note: Check that recipe line starts with tab
    Let has_tab be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "\t"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Backend generates tab for recipe", has_tab, "Contains tab character"

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Round-Trip Tests
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Round-trip check that a simple variable assignment preserves both
the variable name and value through translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
round_trip_translate("CC = gcc"); assert output contains both "CC"
and "gcc".
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "CC = gcc" -> output contains "CC" and "gcc", passed
- Backend loses variable name -> "Contains CC" fails
- Backend loses variable value -> "Contains gcc" fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip_simple_variable" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test round-trip translation of simple variable assignment.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "CC = gcc"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let regenerated be proc round_trip_translate from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Note: Regenerated should preserve semantics (may normalize formatting)
    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves variable assignment", is_valid, "Non-empty output"

    Let contains_cc be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "CC"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves variable name", contains_cc, "Contains CC"

    Let contains_gcc be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "gcc"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves variable value", contains_gcc, "Contains gcc"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Round-trip check that target rule preserves target name and colon
separator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
round_trip_translate target rule; assert output contains "app" and ":".
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- target rule -> output contains "app" and ":", passed
- Backend drops target name -> "Contains app" fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip_target_rule" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test round-trip translation of target rule.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "app: main.o\n\tgcc -o app main.o"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let regenerated be proc round_trip_translate from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves target rule", is_valid, "Non-empty output"

    Let contains_app be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "app"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves target name", contains_app, "Contains app"

    Let contains_colon be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, ":"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves colon", contains_colon, "Contains colon"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Round-trip check that pattern rule preserves "%" pattern and "$@"
automatic variable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
round_trip_translate pattern rule; assert output contains "%" and "$@".
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- pattern rule -> output contains "%" and "$@", passed
- Backend expands "$@" -> "Contains $@" fails (silent transformation)
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip_pattern_rule" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test round-trip translation of pattern rule with %.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "%.o: %.c\n\tgcc -c $< -o $@"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let regenerated be proc round_trip_translate from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves pattern rule", is_valid, "Non-empty output"

    Let contains_percent be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "%"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves % pattern", contains_percent, "Contains %"

    Let contains_auto_target be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "$@"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves $@ automatic variable", contains_auto_target, "Contains $@"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Round-trip check that ifeq conditional preserves the conditional
form through translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
round_trip_translate ifeq conditional; assert output non-empty.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- ifeq block -> non-empty regenerated, passed
- Backend drops conditional -> empty output -> fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip_conditional" that takes suite_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Test round-trip translation of conditional blocks.
    @End Reasoning

    Let source be "ifeq ($(CC),gcc)\nCFLAGS = -O2\nendif"

    Let emitter_ptr be proc create_emitter from MakefileEmitter
    Let regenerated be proc round_trip_translate from MakefileEmitter with emitter_ptr, source

    Let is_valid be proc string_length from StringCore with regenerated is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves conditional", is_valid, "Non-empty output"

    Let contains_ifeq be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "ifeq"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves ifeq", contains_ifeq, "Contains ifeq"

    Let contains_endif be proc string_contains from StringCore with regenerated, "endif"
    proc assert_true with suite_ptr, "Round-trip preserves endif", contains_endif, "Contains endif"

    Return 1
End Process

